FBIS4-778 "drafr073_c_94021" FBIS-AFR-94-073 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Van der Walt: Fair Election Possible Van der Walt: Fair Election Possible MB1504095894 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network in English 0500 GMT 15 Apr 94 MB1504095894 Johannesburg SABC TV 1 Network English BFN [Text] Bophuthatsawana co-adminstartor Tjaart van der Walt has denied reports that the situation in the former homeland is getting out of control. Dr. van der Walt said that while he and his co-administrator, Mr. Job Makgoro, had held heated talks with Bophuthatswana police on pension payouts, he believed that the police were still committed to maintaining law and order. He said that he and Bophuthatswana and South African Police officials were unanimous in feeling that while the situation was volatile, it was not out of control. Dr. van der Walt said that efficiency in the civil service was improving and that it was certain that free and fair elections would be able to go ahead in that territory.
